headline: Synchrony Financial (SYF) Profit Margins Rise to 36.2%, Contradicting Bearish Margin Narratives
summary: Synchrony Financial (SYF) delivered robust results this cycle, with revenue forecast to grow 13.3% per year ahead of the broader US market’s 10% pace. Net profit margin climbed to 36.2%, marking an improvement from 34.5% a year ago, while earnings growth accelerated to 12.5% over the past year compared to the five-year average of 3.9%. Despite profit growth forecasts turning negative at -3.4% per year going forward, SYF’s relative valuation stands out, trading at a 7.7x Price-To-Earnings...

headline: SYF Q3 Deep Dive: Credit Actions and New Partnerships Shape Flat Revenue, Outlook Hinges on Consumer Resilience
summary: Consumer financial services company Synchrony Financial (NYSE:SYF) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, but sales were flat year on year at $3.82 billion. Its GAAP profit of $2.86 per share was 28.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
